description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Sister, Charge Nurse &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking experienced Band 6 Registered Nurses who are enthusiastic and hardworking, and who enjoy new challenges, . Silvertown Ward offers a unique insight into East London life and its associated medical conditions. We strive to deliver a high standard of care to our patients and their families, and provide extensive in-house training. Access to formal courses of education at local universities is available to facilitate professional development. Silvertown Ward is a 24 bedded medical ward caring for Gastroenterology, Haematology and Hepatoloy and respiratory patients,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer a wide range of development opportunities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Band 6 leadership programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;external conferences and courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to be involved in quality improvement methodology training and lead on improvements in the clinical area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you like the sound of this exciting opportunity, we would like to hear from you. .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome informal visits. To arrange a visit or for a discussion, please contact Interim Ward Manager Olah Brown via olah.brown@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
